SUMMARY:The Indie Journalist Meetup
DESCRIPTION:The Creative House of Lancaster\nJoin us for the inaugural gat
 hering of the Indie Journalist Meetup at [The Candy Factory](www.coworking
 inlancaster.com) (TCF)\, 342 N. Queen St.\, Lancaster.\n\nWe’re looking 
 to gather digital journalists from the greater Lancaster area who are navi
 gating the creator economy to produce content covering news\, events\, and
  lifestyle/cultural features. This can include podcasters\, bloggers\, wri
 ters\, livestreamers\, and more.\n\nIn this first meetup\, our goal is to 
 take inventory of what’s happening in our slice of the information ecosy
 stem here in Lancaster. Let’s share the projects we’re working on and 
 what we hope to accomplish with them. We will also brainstorm ideas for wh
 at participants might find valuable as the meetup develops.\n\n**ABOUT THE
  INDIE JOURNALIST MEETUP**\nA meetup for independent journalists covering 
 news\, events\, culture\, and lifestyle while navigating the creator econo
 my in Lancaster and surrounding areas. All creators welcome: podcasters\, 
 freelance writers\, bloggers\, YouTubers\, livestreamers\, and more!\n\nOu
 r mission is to create a space to gather in real life\, to discuss the rew
 ards and challenges of bringing authentic news and information to the Lanc
 aster community\, and to encourage participants to collaborate and share k
 nowledge when appropriate to strengthen our local information ecosystem.\n
 \n**ABOUT YOUR HOST**\nJason Mundok is a seasoned media producer with over
  two decades of experience creating compelling content and leading creativ
 e teams. At So Good Media\, he produces audio podcasts\, marketing videos\
 , and original programming.\n\nHe currently hosts *[So Good Lancaster](htt
 ps://sogoodlancaster.com/)*\, a show that celebrates the people and ideas 
 that make Lancaster\, PA\, so good.\n\nThe Creative House of Lancaster is 
 a project of [The Candy Factory\, a coworking + social club](http://www.co
 workinginlancaster.com/) located in the heart of Lancaster\, PA.
